# ROADMAP - ORIC-1 Emulator

## Vision
Create a cycle-accurate ORIC-1 emulator in C/C++ with modern features including
host filesystem sharing and conversion tools for legacy BASIC/machine code programs.

---

## Phase 1: Foundation (Sprint 1-3) - Q1 2026

### Sprint 1: Core CPU (v0.2.0-alpha)
**Goal**: Implement cycle-accurate 6502 CPU core

#### User Stories
- [ ] As a developer, I want a 6502 CPU that executes all official opcodes
- [ ] As a developer, I want cycle-accurate timing for each instruction
- [ ] As a developer, I want proper flag handling (N, V, Z, C, I, D)
- [ ] As a developer, I want all addressing modes implemented

#### Tasks
- [ ] Implement 6502 instruction set (151 official opcodes)
- [ ] Create CPU state structure (A, X, Y, SP, PC, flags)
- [ ] Implement all addressing modes (13 modes)
- [ ] Create cycle-accurate timing system
- [ ] Write unit tests for each opcode
- [ ] Document CPU architecture

#### Definition of Done
- All official opcodes pass test suite
- Cycle counts verified against hardware specs
- 100% code coverage for CPU core
- API documentation complete

